00:57:41,021 --> 00:57:42,146
[Davis] Not bad at all.

1050
00:57:42,313 --> 00:57:44,438
[Sharon] That is
a beautiful car, though.

1051
00:57:46,063 --> 00:57:47,563
I underestimated you.

1052
00:57:47,730 --> 00:57:48,813
Mike.

1053
00:57:48,980 --> 00:57:50,146
Sharon.

1054
00:57:50,313 --> 00:57:51,480
Nice to meet you, Mike.

1055
00:57:51,646 --> 00:57:53,021
[Davis] Nice to meet you, too.

1056
00:57:59,688 --> 00:58:00,688
- [door closes]
- [engine starts]

1057
00:58:04,230 --> 00:58:05,646
[key clacking]

1058
00:58:06,980 --> 00:58:08,396
- [operator] Like I said...
- [Tillman] No...

1059
00:58:08,563 --> 00:58:10,730
[operator] ...that's
the last image we have.

1060
00:58:10,896 --> 00:58:12,980
[Lou] Are you certain
that we don't pick him up

1061
00:58:13,146 --> 00:58:14,855
on the 101
in either direction?

1062
00:58:15,021 --> 00:58:16,730
[operator sighs]
Still certain.

1063
00:58:19,188 --> 00:58:21,938
Somewhere between that turn
and the 101, he switched cars.

1064
00:58:22,105 --> 00:58:23,480
Why are you so convinced
he took the 101?

1065
00:58:23,646 --> 00:58:24,646
Hey, don't ask, man.

1066
00:58:24,813 --> 00:58:27,230
Look, there's 30 blocks
between there and the 101.

1067
00:58:27,396 --> 00:58:28,646
- Let's get lookin'.
- Are you serious?

1068
00:58:28,813 --> 00:58:30,521
- [Lou] I'm serious.
- Lou, come on, man.

1069
00:58:30,688 --> 00:58:31,813
[Lou] How else
are we gonna find him?

1070
00:58:32,480 --> 00:58:34,313
[Maya] The books
come with the place?

1071
00:58:34,730 --> 00:58:36,188
- Uh-huh.
- [Maya] Huh.

1072
00:58:38,855 --> 00:58:40,188
For someone
who likes things...

1073
00:58:40,355 --> 00:58:41,980
you don't
really have a lot of...

1074
00:58:43,146 --> 00:58:44,438
personal stuff.

1075
00:58:46,855 --> 00:58:48,771
No photos of family or...

1076
00:58:52,021 --> 00:58:53,313
Do you have any?

1077
00:58:53,480 --> 00:58:54,563
What? Photos?

1078
00:58:54,730 --> 00:58:56,688
[chuckles] No. Family.

1079
00:58:57,605 --> 00:58:58,605
Yeah, someplace.

1080
00:58:59,230 --> 00:59:00,355
Someplace?

1081
00:59:00,521 --> 00:59:01,855
- What, like in a drawer?
- [Davis chuckles]

1082
00:59:02,563 --> 00:59:04,355
I don't know, we're just
not really that kinda family.

1083
00:59:04,521 --> 00:59:05,813
Don't really keep in touch.

1084
00:59:05,980 --> 00:59:07,021
I don't know.

1085
00:59:07,188 --> 00:59:09,521
Do you have,
like, brothers? Sisters?

1086
00:59:09,688 --> 00:59:11,605
- Mom? Dad?
- [knife clangs]

1087
00:59:12,980 --> 00:59:14,855
Yeah. Yeah.

1088
00:59:15,021 --> 00:59:16,438
I don't know,
we didn't really, uh,

1089
00:59:16,605 --> 00:59:17,771
have a lot of stuff growin' up

1090
00:59:17,938 --> 00:59:19,438
and whatever we did have,

1091
00:59:19,605 --> 00:59:20,896
I didn't really
keep any of it.

1092
00:59:22,438 --> 00:59:23,438
So...

1093
00:59:24,355 --> 00:59:26,355
[mellow music playing]

1094
00:59:34,938 --> 00:59:35,938
What?

1095
00:59:36,730 --> 00:59:38,021
Mystery man.

1096
00:59:43,105 --> 00:59:44,188
Yeah.

1097
00:59:44,896 --> 00:59:46,938
[Maya] Can I turn on
some music?

1098
00:59:47,855 --> 00:59:48,980
[Davis] Yeah.

1099
00:59:49,146 --> 00:59:51,563
There's a thing in the corner.

1100
00:59:53,646 --> 00:59:54,730
Do you have a favorite song?

1101
00:59:56,730 --> 00:59:58,271
Um...

1102
00:59:58,438 --> 01:00:00,105
[Maya] No. Okay.

1103
01:00:00,271 --> 01:00:01,521
I don't know why I would ask

1104
01:00:01,688 --> 01:00:04,105
why you would have
a favorite song.

1105
01:00:04,271 --> 01:00:06,230
[Davis] Suppose that's
another black mark, huh?

1106
01:00:06,396 --> 01:00:07,396
[Maya chuckles]

1107
01:00:08,188 --> 01:00:09,355
[Maya] Aye, yai, yai...

1108
01:00:09,521 --> 01:00:11,146
- Do you, um...
- [device beeps]

1109
01:00:11,313 --> 01:00:13,271
Do you listen to music or...

1110
01:00:13,896 --> 01:00:14,979
Yeah, sometimes.

1111
01:00:14,980 --> 01:00:15,937
[soft rock song playing]

1112
01:00:15,938 --> 01:00:17,271
[Maya] Sometimes?

1113
01:00:18,438 --> 01:00:19,605
You don't, do you?

1114
01:00:24,855 --> 01:00:26,063
Come on.

1115
01:00:27,730 --> 01:00:29,146
I can't dance.

1116
01:00:36,396 --> 01:00:37,480
Come on.

1117
01:00:38,563 --> 01:00:39,980
Come on.

1118
01:00:42,646 --> 01:00:43,646
Come here.

1119
01:00:43,813 --> 01:00:47,563
No photos,
no music, no dancing.

1120
01:00:48,188 --> 01:00:51,271
Someone needs to teach you
how to be a human.

1121
01:00:51,438 --> 01:00:52,438
Yeah.

1122
01:00:55,646 --> 01:00:56,730
[Maya laughs]

1123
01:00:59,438 --> 01:01:01,063
[crowd cheering
over music player]

1124
01:01:01,230 --> 01:01:02,313
Ah.

1125
01:01:03,230 --> 01:01:04,563
I love that.

1126
01:01:05,730 --> 01:01:09,646
They cheer for home,
but no one does that for LA.

1127
01:01:16,771 --> 01:01:18,105
[crowd cheering
over music player]

1128
01:02:07,813 --> 01:02:08,813
[song fades]

1129
01:02:10,021 --> 01:02:11,105
[Maya] Happy?

1130
01:02:14,438 --> 01:02:15,438
Yeah.

1131
01:02:19,771 --> 01:02:20,813
Yeah.

1132
01:02:25,855 --> 01:02:26,855
Scared?

1133
01:02:31,896 --> 01:02:32,980
Yeah, maybe.

1134
01:02:35,563 --> 01:02:36,563
[exhales]

1135
01:02:36,730 --> 01:02:38,730
[mellow music playing]

1136
01:02:53,605 --> 01:02:54,813
You're not gonna stay?

1137
01:03:08,438 --> 01:03:09,438
[exhales softly]

1138
01:03:14,105 --> 01:03:15,521
[Maya] Do you want me to stay?

1139
01:03:17,146 --> 01:03:18,146
[Davis] Yeah.

1140
01:03:25,271 --> 01:03:26,355
Good.

1141
01:03:34,855 --> 01:03:35,855
[door opens]

1142
01:03:40,480 --> 01:03:41,313
[door closes]

1143
01:04:00,438 --> 01:04:02,438
[tense music playing]

1144
01:04:20,938 --> 01:04:22,313
[engine starts]

1145
01:04:35,063 --> 01:04:36,105
[breathing heavily]

1146
01:04:41,563 --> 01:04:42,605
[grunts]

1147
01:04:42,771 --> 01:04:44,730
[panting]

1148
01:04:45,271 --> 01:04:46,105
[Davis grunts]

1149
01:04:57,188 --> 01:04:58,188
[line beeps]

1150
01:04:58,355 --> 01:05:00,146
[Davis] Hi, this is Mr. Stone.

1151
01:05:00,313 --> 01:05:01,271
I need a new apartment

1152
01:05:01,438 --> 01:05:03,813
on the beach
available immediately.

1153
01:05:06,105 --> 01:05:06,938
[door thuds]

1154
01:05:22,480 --> 01:05:24,605
[doorbell buzzing]

1155
01:05:29,855 --> 01:05:30,855
[Devon] Can I help you?

1156
01:05:31,021 --> 01:05:32,021
[Ormon] Got delivery
for Wilson.

1157
01:05:32,188 --> 01:05:33,813
I'm not expecting anything.

1158
01:05:33,980 --> 01:05:35,146
[Ormon] It's got
your name on it.

1159
01:05:35,313 --> 01:05:37,605
All right.
Just leave it outside.

1160
01:05:37,771 --> 01:05:38,646
[Ormon] I'm not allowed
to do that.

1161
01:05:38,813 --> 01:05:40,146
[sighs] All right.
Leave it in the hall.

1162
01:05:40,313 --> 01:05:41,313
[door buzzes]

1163
01:05:47,938 --> 01:05:49,063
- [door thuds]
- [Devon] Whoa!

1164
01:05:49,230 --> 01:05:50,605
[Devon gasping]

1165
01:05:50,771 --> 01:05:53,938
[Ormon] Move.
Come on, move. Move.

1166
01:05:54,730 --> 01:05:56,688
[both grunting]

1167
01:05:59,313 --> 01:06:00,188
Huh?

1168
01:06:02,146 --> 01:06:04,563
You're gonna tell me what you
fucking gave him, okay?

1169
01:06:05,813 --> 01:06:06,937
Fucking tell me.

1170
01:06:06,938 --> 01:06:07,938
[panting]

1171
01:06:09,855 --> 01:06:10,813
[Tillman] How many
more of these

1172
01:06:10,980 --> 01:06:12,688
fucking garages you gonna
make us do tonight, man?

1173
01:06:13,813 --> 01:06:15,105
[Tillman sighs]

1174
01:06:15,271 --> 01:06:16,271
Hey, man...

1175
01:06:19,438 --> 01:06:21,188
- Let's take a look.
- Have you...

1176
01:06:21,355 --> 01:06:23,605
- See there?
- What? Now what?

1177
01:06:34,563 --> 01:06:35,480
Lou.

1178
01:06:35,646 --> 01:06:36,646
[car alarm beeping]

1179
01:06:37,230 --> 01:06:38,063
[sighs deeply]

1180
01:06:38,605 --> 01:06:40,438
Fuck's sake, man.

1181
01:06:51,896 --> 01:06:53,146
[mumbles] Mmm. Huh.

1182
01:06:58,771 --> 01:06:59,771
Call forensics.

1183
01:06:59,938 --> 01:07:01,521
[man] Black
wasn't a color for him.

1184
01:07:01,688 --> 01:07:03,355
It was his whole subject.

1185
01:07:03,521 --> 01:07:04,563
[woman] I wouldn't
put it on my wall

1186
01:07:04,730 --> 01:07:07,146
but I do love
the sense of drama.

1187
01:07:07,313 --> 01:07:10,063
I think you can be confident
it's not gonna lose its value.

1188
01:07:10,230 --> 01:07:11,813
The real question is...

1189
01:07:11,980 --> 01:07:13,271
how much do you love it?

1190
01:07:13,438 --> 01:07:14,646
Well, I love it.

1191
01:07:14,813 --> 01:07:16,605
It'll go great
with the new chairs, you know.

1192
01:07:16,771 --> 01:07:18,438
[Andrew] Really?
You sure you want this guy

1193
01:07:18,605 --> 01:07:21,062
glaring down at us
every time we have dinner?

1194
01:07:21,063 --> 01:07:22,062
[Beth] He's not glaring.

1195
01:07:22,063 --> 01:07:23,146
[Andrew] He's glaring.

1196
01:07:23,313 --> 01:07:25,271
[Beth] I'm sure.
And he isn't glaring, really.

1197
01:07:25,438 --> 01:07:26,270
He's just looking, you know.

1198
01:07:26,271 --> 01:07:27,312
Excuse me.
I'll be right with you.

1199
01:07:27,313 --> 01:07:28,396
- [Beth] Okay.
- Sure. Thank you.

1200
01:07:30,896 --> 01:07:32,730
Well, what a coincidence.

1201
01:07:32,896 --> 01:07:33,896
[Davis] Hey.

1202
01:07:34,063 --> 01:07:35,063
Uh, Sharon, right?

1203
01:07:35,230 --> 01:07:36,230
- [Sharon] Yeah.
- Yeah.

1204
01:07:36,396 --> 01:07:37,813
- Mike?
- That's it.

1205
01:07:37,980 --> 01:07:39,271
- Yeah, good to see you.
- [Sharon] Hmm.

1206
01:07:40,646 --> 01:07:41,480
Uh...

1207
01:07:42,063 --> 01:07:44,563
So do you collect art
like you do cars, Mike?

1208
01:07:44,730 --> 01:07:46,146
Uh, not really, but I like it.

1209
01:07:47,188 --> 01:07:48,938
I like the sense of drama.

1210
01:07:49,480 --> 01:07:51,521
[glass clinking]

1211
01:07:52,146 --> 01:07:52,980
[Sharon] Hmm.

1212
01:07:55,396 --> 01:07:57,230
Hey, do you maybe
wanna get out of here?

1213
01:07:57,396 --> 01:07:59,230
Grab a drink or something?

1214
01:08:00,105 --> 01:08:01,855
[Tillman] I swear, man...

1215
01:08:02,021 --> 01:08:03,313
you divorced guys,
you always think

1216
01:08:03,480 --> 01:08:04,313
you're gonna move to the beach

1217
01:08:04,480 --> 01:08:06,271
and meet
some hot surfer chick.

1218
01:08:06,438 --> 01:08:08,355
What you gonna do?
Take up surfing?

1219
01:08:08,521 --> 01:08:11,271
No. I'm gonna...
Thinking of doing the yoga.

1220
01:08:12,521 --> 01:08:13,730
The yoga?

1221
01:08:15,271 --> 01:08:16,480
[Tillman laughs]

1222
01:08:16,646 --> 01:08:18,813
'Course, you are. What kind?

1223
01:08:19,480 --> 01:08:20,688
They got kinds?

1224
01:08:20,855 --> 01:08:22,105
Big time, man.

1225
01:08:22,271 --> 01:08:25,480
They got hot yoga, fast yoga,

1226
01:08:25,646 --> 01:08:27,563
street yoga, Greek yoga.

1227
01:08:27,730 --> 01:08:29,730
- Greek yoga?
- That last one might be food.

1228
01:08:29,896 --> 01:08:31,313
[Tillman chuckling]

1229
01:08:31,480 --> 01:08:33,188
So, you just wanna get laid.

1230
01:08:33,355 --> 01:08:34,396
Oh, man, I wanna get fit.

1231
01:08:34,563 --> 01:08:35,938
- Fitness?
- [sighs]

1232
01:08:36,105 --> 01:08:38,105
- Please, booze man, you...
- [Lou] What's up?

1233
01:08:38,271 --> 01:08:39,521
It's like a new car.

1234
01:08:39,688 --> 01:08:41,063
Fuck.

1235
01:08:41,230 --> 01:08:43,271
Except for one
microscopic speck of blood.

1236
01:08:44,605 --> 01:08:46,313
[Tillman] Is it enough
to get DNA?

1237
01:08:46,480 --> 01:08:47,730
[forensics officer] Should be.

1238
01:08:47,896 --> 01:08:49,063
Let me see.

1239
01:08:51,021 --> 01:08:52,938
[Davis] So, I guess
you work in the art world?

1240
01:08:53,605 --> 01:08:55,271
[Sharon] Nope. Less glamorous.

1241
01:08:55,438 --> 01:08:57,896
I write insurance policies
for people

1242
01:08:58,063 --> 01:09:00,146
who have more money than
they know what to do with.

1243
01:09:00,938 --> 01:09:01,812
[Davis] So, you must know

1244
01:09:01,813 --> 01:09:03,105
a lot about
what things are worth, huh?

1245
01:09:03,271 --> 01:09:05,480
Mmm-hmm. Too much.

1246
01:09:05,646 --> 01:09:06,980
But I also have to know a lot

1247
01:09:07,146 --> 01:09:09,020
about the people
that own these things.

1248
01:09:09,021 --> 01:09:10,020
How do you mean?

1249
01:09:10,021 --> 01:09:11,605
[Sharon] You know,
are you a thrill seeker,

1250
01:09:12,188 --> 01:09:14,230
are you an alcoholic,
do you gamble,

1251
01:09:14,396 --> 01:09:15,605
do you cheat on your partner?

1252
01:09:15,771 --> 01:09:17,480
You know, all those questions
that you can't ask

1253
01:09:17,646 --> 01:09:19,980
but you obviously need to know
the answers to.

1254
01:09:20,813 --> 01:09:23,438
So, you get real good
at reading people.

1255
01:09:23,896 --> 01:09:26,271
And what have you,
uh, read about me?

1256
01:09:27,105 --> 01:09:28,355
[Sharon chuckles]

1257
01:09:28,521 --> 01:09:29,521
Mmm-mmm.

1258
01:09:30,355 --> 01:09:31,645
Things you don't like or what?

1259
01:09:31,646 --> 01:09:32,645
[Sharon] Mmm-mmm.

1260
01:09:32,646 --> 01:09:34,855
Nope. No, did not say that.

1261
01:09:36,146 --> 01:09:36,979
[Sharon chuckles]

1262
01:09:36,980 --> 01:09:38,230
Come on.

1263
01:09:40,813 --> 01:09:41,813
Okay.

1264
01:09:42,730 --> 01:09:46,021
[sighs] Well, you look like
a person who has secrets.

1265
01:09:46,188 --> 01:09:47,646
- Is that right?
- [Sharon] Mmm-hmm.

1266
01:09:47,813 --> 01:09:49,688
Your shirt's new
or newly pressed

1267
01:09:49,855 --> 01:09:51,813
which says you don't
do your own laundry

1268
01:09:51,980 --> 01:09:53,230
or you're a bit OCD.

1269
01:09:53,396 --> 01:09:54,646
Uh, you're very groomed.

1270
01:09:55,021 --> 01:09:56,521
Your hair, your nails,

1271
01:09:56,688 --> 01:09:58,688
your 12-thousand-dollar
watch there,

1272
01:09:59,355 --> 01:10:00,980
everything is just, uh...

1273
01:10:02,105 --> 01:10:03,480
a little too perfect.

1274
01:10:03,646 --> 01:10:05,146
Which tells me
you have a lot of money

1275
01:10:05,313 --> 01:10:07,230
and a lot of time
on your hands, Mike.

1276
01:10:08,063 --> 01:10:09,396
Got the clothes, the cars...

1277
01:10:09,563 --> 01:10:11,688
but you can't seem
to look me in the eye.

1278
01:10:11,855 --> 01:10:14,771
And I'd bet
you didn't grow up with money.

1279
01:10:16,605 --> 01:10:17,605
How do you figure that?

1280
01:10:17,938 --> 01:10:21,271
Because people who grow up
in chaos crave order.

1281
01:10:24,146 --> 01:10:25,771
You talkin' about me or you?

1282
01:10:27,188 --> 01:10:28,396
Maybe both.

1283
01:10:31,313 --> 01:10:32,896
That hit too close to home?

1284
01:10:34,896 --> 01:10:35,896
No.

1285
01:10:38,813 --> 01:10:40,146
I have a...

1286
01:10:40,813 --> 01:10:42,813
[clears throat]
I have a confession to make.

1287
01:10:42,980 --> 01:10:43,980
[Sharon] Really?

1288
01:10:44,646 --> 01:10:46,146
[laughs] I haven't even
finished my drink.

1289
01:10:46,313 --> 01:10:49,646
This wasn't a coincidence.
Us meeting again.

1290
01:10:51,855 --> 01:10:52,688
Oh.

1291
01:10:53,396 --> 01:10:55,021
I came here to talk to you.

1292
01:10:55,188 --> 01:10:56,188
You followed me?

1293
01:10:56,355 --> 01:10:58,980
I came here to make you
a business proposition.

1294
01:11:01,646 --> 01:11:04,813
You see, I know some things
about you, too, Sharon.

1295
01:11:05,813 --> 01:11:07,605
Really? Like what?

1296
01:11:07,771 --> 01:11:09,021
You live alone.
You're not married.

1297
01:11:09,188 --> 01:11:10,646
You never have been.

1298
01:11:10,813 --> 01:11:11,896
No children.

1299
01:11:12,063 --> 01:11:13,688
You've worked at the same
company for 11 years.

1300
01:11:13,855 --> 01:11:15,938
You're a VP when you
should be a partner.

1301
01:11:16,105 --> 01:11:16,980
Uh-huh. Who the fuck are you?

1302
01:11:17,146 --> 01:11:18,062
[Davis] Just give me
30 seconds.

1303
01:11:18,063 --> 01:11:18,979
No. I...

1304
01:11:18,980 --> 01:11:20,313
[Davis] What
I have to offer you

1305
01:11:20,480 --> 01:11:22,146
is zero risk to you
and a huge upside,

1306
01:11:22,313 --> 01:11:23,438
a life-changing upside.

1307
01:11:23,605 --> 01:11:25,605
